column2: Deeper than Webb south- but less clear.
Lake level stable- no rain- water temp mid-50's.
Little rain in last 7 days- water temp. and weeds seem ahead for the season.
Clear- calm- sunny- pollen- lily pad growth way ahead of schedule.
Little rain in the last 7 days- water temperatures and weeds seem ahead for the season.
Continued excessive weed growth and scummy algae floating- rained 1" during week.
Weed growth appears to be 10-15 days ahead.
Sunny- no rain- algae bloom- and the temperature is 75 degrees F.
Weeds appearing on surface and some going to seed- rained 1.2" on 7/23/1987- and the weather is partly cloudy.
Weeds prolific- large areas of maturing coontail on surface- 1.5" of rain during week- sunny.
A lot of surface weeds have died off and sunk.
Windy storm with .5-.75" of rain on 8/15- sunny- windy.
Weeds still present near and on surface- sunny.
Weeds on surface still present- water temp. 68 F- cloudy.
Still has surface weeds and green film- sunny- calm.
Water temp. 56 F- rained .5" this week- sunny.
Sunny- rained .25" this week- water temp. 46 F.
Cloudy- water temp. at secchi depth and surface is 50 F- rained .25" this week.
Partly cloudy- water temp. at surface and at secchi depth is 48 F- rained .75" this week.
Sunny- no rain this week- last report of the season.
Sunny- water temp 51 F- suspended sediment.
Sunny- rain/snow this week- water 51 F.  Considerable micro organisms or vegetation bloom.  Sunny with southwest wind at 5 mph.
8 weeks. no rain- sunny- floating decayed weeds- water 58 @ surface.  Sunny with southwest wind at 10 mph.
Sunny- SE wind @ 10 mph- received .8" rain 5/7/88- water temp. 65 F- floating- decaying weeds now washing up on shore.  Water quality is excellent to very good. Water level up 1"
Received 1" of rain this week- partly sunny- water temp. 66 F- cotton bloom on water. Water level up 1"
Water temp. 69 F- received .1" rain this week. cloudy west wind at 10-15 mph.  Seed cotton heavy on lake.
25" rain this week- water 75 F- tree pollen and seed blooms cover.  West to southwest wind at 15 mph.
.25 rain this week- water 82 F.  Sunny and west to southwest wind at 5 mph.
Water 77 F- curly leaf pondweed near surface- hazy sun.
Some weeds at surface- heavy boat traffic has reduced clarity- wind W 10-15- water 79 F.
Partly cloudy- wind NE @ 5 mph- increased weeds on surface- water temp. 79 F.  Tree swallows leaving nest.
.75" rain- opinion effected by weeds- sunny- west wind at 5-10 mph- water 76 F.  Weeds.
Opinion effected by weeds- water 75 F- weeds reach surface- sunny- wind NW 10 mph.
Opinion effected by weeds- coontail near surface- water 78 F- cloudy.
Opinion based on weeds- water 76 F- coontail underwater- scum on surface- sunny with northwest wind at 5 -10 mph.
Same- rain.4" this week- water 86 F algae heavy but not as bad as previous years. Sunny with southeast winds at 10-15 mph. Weeds.
Weeds- water 83 F- sunny west-southwest 10-15 mph.  Minor weed problem so far.  Water level: up 2"
Weeds- water 84 F- minor weeds on surface (coontail)- 3" rain this week- partly cloudy- wind NW 5-10.
Weeds- water 70 F- cooler weather- cloudy- wind SE 0-5.  The temperature at night is 55-60 degrees and during the day it is 70-75 degrees.
Late summer change over- no occurring weed problem- weeds at minimum for 1988- clouds- wind NW 10-15- cool weather predominates. Water level up 1"
Weeds dying off- .8" rain- water temp 65 F- air 60-65 F.  Partly cloudy with northeast wind at 15 mph.
Algae suspended throughout water- hazy sun- water 64 F.  West wind at 5-10 mph.  Weeds at peak.
Sunny- calm- 1.2" rain- suspended algae on surface.  Weeds at peak. Water level up 1"
4" rain this week- water temp 60 F- suspended algae throughout water.  Weeds on surface are dying.  Sunny with northwest wind at 5 mph.  Water level: up 3.75"
.5" rain- weeds dying off- water 58 F- cloudy- west wind at 5 mph.
Water 51 F- .1" rain this week- calm- cloudy- surface weeds still present.
Sunny- w-southwest wind- .8" rain in last week- water temp 48 F.
Lots of birds- incl. loons/can. geese- lake temp. 45 F. Water level up 1"
W. temp. 49 F.  Water level up 1/2"
Sunny and northeast wind at 0-5 mph.  Water temperature is 62 degrees.
Considerable amount of weeds- sunny- winds W 5-10 mph.  Water level: up 1 1/2"
Water temperature. 62 F- down 2 degrees in 2 days- cloudy east-northeast wind 15 mph.  Water level: up 1 1/2"
Water temp. 65 F- rec. .7 in. rain this week.
Water temp. 66 F- considerable floating vegetation- sunny SW wind 5-10 mph.
Sunny- W wind 5-10 mph- water temperature. 72 F- .6 in. rain.  Water level up 1/2"
Excessive cut floating weeds from boats- water temperature 77 F- sunny- NW wind 10-15 mph.  Water level: up 1 1/2"
Sunny- calm- no rain for 17 days- weeds.
Water temp. 80 F- hazy- S wind 0-5 mph- weeds.
Cloudy- calm- 1.1" rain since last- weeds. Water level up 1"
Cloudy- NE wind 15-20 mph- weeds at peak- water temp. 74 F.
Cloudy- N wind 0-5 mph- water 72.8 F- weeds peaking- rec. 2 in. rain this week.  The water is semi clear.  Water level: up 2"
Partly cloudy- N wind 10-15 mph- water 72.3 F- weeds peaking- rec. .7 in. rain this week.  The water has a greenish tint.  Water level: up .3"
Sunny- NW wind 0-5 mph- water temp. 73.8 F- particulate algae.  The water is semi clear with a greenish tint.  Water level up 1/2"
Partly cloudy- SW wind 5 mph- water temp. 69 F- 4.5 in. rain recently.
Weeds on surface- sunny- SW wind 5-10 mph- water 66 F- level down from 9/4 but still high.
Sunny- SW wind 10-15 mph- .6 in. rain this week- water 61.2 F.
Sunny- SW wind 15-20 mph- beaver closed channel b/w lakes- no rain.
Beavers keeping level high + passage blocked- weeds still peaking- water 55.6 F- sunny- N wind 0-5 mph.
Hazy- SW wind 0-5 mph- water 50.7 F.  Water level variable
Cloudy- SW wind 0-5 mph- last report.
Sunny- SW wind 10 mph- water 44 F.
Hazy- S wind 15-20 mph- water 49.5 F.
Cloudy- E wind 0-5 mph.  Beavers have lake outlet dammed- water over banks in low areas.  Water level: up 4"
Sunny- W wind 5-10 mph- water temp. 57.2 F.
Sunny- E wind 20-25 mph- 55.5 F.  Water level up 1/2"
Water surface 63.8 F- heavy boat traffic.  Hazy and northeast wind at 15-25 mph.  Water level up 1/2"
Water surface 63 F- NNW wind at 15-20 mph- and cloudy.  .8" of rain.
Water surface 67.7 F- cloudy- west wind at 5-10 mph- and .9" of rain.  Water level: up 3/4"
Water surface 68.2 F- cloudy- west wind at 0-5 mph- and 1.2" of rain. Water level up 1"
Water surface 70.1 F- sunny- north wind at 5-10 mph- and .3" of rain.
Hazy- SE wind 0-5 mph- water 77.3 F- 3.5" rain past week.  Water level: up 1 1/2"
Partly cloudy- NW wind 10-15 mph- water 75.3 F.
Curly pondweed going to seed- partly cloudy- NW wind 0-5 mph.
Considerable algae- water surface 76.3 F- sunny- NE wind 10-15 mph- 1.7" rain this week. Water level up 1"
Weeds very thick this year- 1" rain.
Heavy weeds- N wind 5-10 mph- water 72 F- 1" rain. Water level up 1"
Weeds dying- partly cloudy- W wind 0-5 mph- water is 75.6 F. rain 1 1/4". Water level up 1"
Sunny- wind 0-5 mph- 1.25" rain. Water level up 1"
Water 73.2 F- cloudy- S wind- 3.3" rain recently.  Water level: up 4.5"
Water 64.5 F- the water was high two weeks ago also.  Rain 1.8".
Sunny- southwest wind at 0-5 mph- and no rain.
Partly cloudy- N wind 10-15 mph- water 55 F- rain .6".  Surprised that the look of clarity- lake appears to have undergone turnover.  We have received heavy winds the last several days.
Water 49 F.  The perception is 3 due to dying weeds. Partly cloudy and northwest winds at 10 mph.  Water level: up 2"
Final reading.  Windy and northwest wind at 15-20 mph- and no rain.
Ice out: 4/3- dead floating weeds- surface temperature is 48 F- and at the secchi depth the temperature is 44.8 F.  Hazy sun with south wind at 5-10 mph.
Sunny- winds: SW at 10-15- surface temp.: 53.3 F.
2.5" of rain- water surface temperature is 49.9 F.  No secchi depth given.  Dropped 10 degrees since last week.  Water level: up 2"
Sunny- green algae in shallows and bottom- temp.: 64 F- received 1.5" of rain. Water level up 1"
Water temp.: 62.4 F- sunny.  Water level up 1/2"
Partly cloudy- breeze- water temperature is 72 F- and received 2.7" of rain.  Water level: up 2"
Received 1.25" of rain- water temp: 73.1 F.  Water level up 1/2"
Surface temp: 74.4 F.  Sunny and northwest wind at 5-10 mph.
Surface temperature is 74.5 F- .8" rain recently- sunny- northwest winds at 5-10 mph.
Hazy- south winds at 5-10mph- water temperature is 73.7 F- and loon chick hatch 6/24. Water level up 1"
Partly cloudy- southwest wind at 5 mph- 3.5" rain recently- and water temperature is 76.2 F.  Water level: up 2"
Weeds within 2 weeks of peaking- earlier this year by 1 week- water temperature is 76.2 F- sunny- and southwest  wind at 5-10 mph.
Surface weeds- surface temperature is 80 F- .5" rain recently- cloudy- winds from northeast at 0-5 mph. Water level up 1"
Surface temperature is 72 F- partly cloudy- winds from the east at 10 mph- and .8" of rain recently.
Sunny.  Surface temperature is 74 degrees.  Heavy algae bloom on lake.  Water level: up 3"
Calm- sunny- recently .1" of rain- and water temperature is 78 degrees.  Floating coontail.  Water level: up 2"
Partly cloudy- northeast wind at 0-5 mph- surface weeds have disappeared- and water temperature is 76 degrees.
Hot week of 85-90 degree temperatures.  Hazy and southwest wind at 5-10 mph.
Water temp: 70 F.  The rainfall from 9/2-9/8 is 4.0".  Water level: up 3 1/2"
Water temp: 61 F- sunny- winds SW at 5-10 mph- and received 3" of rain.  Water level: up 4"
Same as Site 1- water temp: 58 F- lake clearing up.
Northwest wind at 10-15 mph- .65" rain- water temp: 54 F.  Water level: Up 3/4"
Water temp: 52 F.  Weeds still dying off.  Water level up .25"
Surface temp: 49 F- .25" rain.  Water level up .25"
Surface temp: 48 F- .75" rain- water highest all year.  Water level: Up 3/4"
Water temp: 50 degrees.  Partly cloudy.  Wind N 0-5 mph. Lake level down 1 1/2"- but still above average.
Water temp: 58 degrees. Wind SW 10-15 mph. No rain- but lake is still high.
Water temp: 62 degrees. Recorded 1" of rain. Wind 0-5. Cloudy.
Water temp: 62 degrees- one pair of loons nesting. Wind E 0-5 mph.  Cloudy.  Recorded 0.8" rain.
Surface temp: 69 degrees. Wind NW 2-4 mph.  Sunny. Beaver dam removed.  Lake dropped. No rain recorded
Loon chick hatched 6/7/92.  First loon chick hatched 6-7-92.  Sunny + calm. Recorded 3/4" of rain.
12" rain. Cloudy. Wind NE 5-10. Surface temp 76 F.
Surface temp. is 64 degrees. Sunny. Wind NE 10-15.  Recent 2 3/4" rain.
Loon chick hatched today.  Sunny. Wind NW 10-15. recent 3/4" rain. Water level: Up 3/4"
Heavy rain- runoff has made water turbid. Cloudy. Wind NW 15-20. Recent 4 1/2" of rain.  Water level: Up 5"
Surface temp is 72 degrees. Wind NE 10-15 mph. Cloudy. recorded 2" of rain.
Water temp at the surface is 70 degrees. Wind WNW 0-5.  Partly cloudy.  Recorded 1/2" of rain.  Lake level: Still up 2"
Water temp is 74 degrees.  Sunny. Calm. Recorded 1/2" rain. Weeds reaching their peak.  Water level: up 2.5"
Recorded .5" of rain. Weeds at peak- but less than other years.  Surface temp 76 F wind NE 5-10. Partly cloudy.  Water level: Up 1" from normal
Surface temp is 70 degrees. Recorded .4" of rain. Cloudy. Wind W 0-5 mph.
Surface temp is 69 degrees. Recorded 1.3" of rain. Sunny.  Wind W 5-10 mph. Water level up 1"
Surface temp is 66 degrees- some weed beds have died off. Cloudy. Wind NW 15-20. recorded 2.3" of rain.  Water level: Up 2" from normal
Water temp is 67 degrees. Cloudy. Wind S 15-20. Recorded 0.8" of rain.  Water level: up 2"
Surface temp is 65 degrees. Sunny. Wind W 10-15.  Recorded 1.6" of rain.  Water level: up 2"
Surface temp is 60 degrees. Sunny wind W 0-5 mph. No rain.  Lake level:  Stable / Normal
Surface temp is 60 degrees. Sunny. Wind E 0-5 mph. No rain.
Water temp is 56 degrees. Recorded 1 3/4" rain.  Water level: up 1 1/2"
No rain. Surface temp 48 F.  The lake has a late bloom in fall.  Lake level:  Stable to normal conditions
Surface temp. 51 degrees. Sunny. Wind SW 5-10 mph. recorded 1/2" rain.
Surface temp is 59 degrees- loons are building a nest.
Surface water temp 66- both loon chicks fine at 2 weeks.
Weed growth nearing peak- surface water temp 74- .5" rain.
.33" rain- high weed levels- surface water temp 73.
.75" rain- high weed levels- surface water temp 72 F.
Surface temp is 64 degrees.  Lake temperature up 6 degrees from 9/10 to 9/13.
Weeds still healthy.  Looks like fall turnover has occurred.  Surface temperature is 59 degrees.
Surface temp. 46 degrees.  No secchi depth given.
Clearest the lake has been in years.
Weeds on surface are more abundant and prolific than previous two cooler years.
Weeds on surface are more abundant than previous two years.
Appears the lake turnover is occurring earlier this year- considerable weed die back occurred during middle of August and cold water appears to be causing earlier changes.
Mature loons still present- weeds present longer on surface this year.
Weeds are still present in north basin.
End of season- surface temp is 48 degrees.
Surface temp. 55.  Water level: Up 2" rec. .6" rain
Surface temp. 62 degrees. Water level: Up 2.25" rec. 1.3" rain
Surface temp. 64 degrees.  Water level: Up .5" rec. 0" rain
Surface temp. 64 degrees.  Water level: Up 1" rec. 1.4" rain
Removed 4 beaver dams has had an effect on lake level.
Surface temp. 73 degrees. Water level: Up 4" rec 2.8" rain
Surface temp. 80 degrees.  Water level: Up 2" rec. 5" rain
Some surface weeds still present. Water level up 1"
Greenish bloom.  The surface temperature is 48 degrees.  Water level up 1/2"
End of season.  Water level: up 1 1/2"
Surface temperature is 60 degrees.  Water level: Up 1.5" rec. 2" of rain
Decayed weeds are on lake surface.
Unable to filter more than 375 ml due to filter saturation.  Heavy rains preceding tests.  Water level: up 3"
Surface temperature is 76 degrees.  Water level: up 2"
Surface temperature is 72 degrees.  The water is greenish blue.  Water level up 9"
Surface temperature is 78 degrees. Water level: up 2.5"
Surface temperature is 74 degrees.  Water level: up 2.25"
Weed growth doesn't appear to be as heavy this year.  Have had rain every day for eight days.
Surface 78 F.  Water level: Up 2.75 rec. 1.9" rain
Surface temperature is 56 degrees. Lake level:  Stable-rec. .6" rain
Weeds have died back in this lake to their winter status- surface temp is 48 degrees.  Immature loon still on lake.  Water level up 1/2"
End of season!  Water level: Up 1" rec. 1.4" rain
Turnover may be occurring.  Ice out in Upper Webb 4-18-97 and Lower Webb 4-19-97.
Loons not nesting yet.  Lake cold.  Site 1 is 54 degrees. Site 2 is 52 degrees.
Surface temp site 1 = 50 degrees. site 2 = 52 degrees.
Rain gauge reading from 5/1/97 to 5/20/97 = 0.75 inches.
Little rain for 3 months since 4-1-97.  Rain gauge reading from 6/16/97 to 6/23/97 = 0.25 inches.
Rain gauge reading from 7/23/97 to 7/28/97 = 2.2 inches.
Department of Natural Resources has authorized the drawdown on the Webb Lake dam by 2'- the lake May also drop but how much is unknown- it could affect readings.  Water level up 1.75"
Rain gauge reading from 8/28/97 to 9/2/97 = 2 inches.
Shallow weeds are dying- surface temp is 62 degrees.
Surface temp 50 degrees- lake is still loaded with algae and weeds.
North basin- east end very turbid.  Light milk chocolate- 62 degrees.
Received 2.7 inches of rain.  Level normal: 12 inches.
Received 3.2 inches of rain.  Dock at 10.75 inches  73 degrees.
Weeds at peak in north basin.
Surface water temp. 62 degrees.  Young loon present.
Recorded 2" rain since 5/5/99.  Water temp 60 deg F.
Parts of lake light chocolate color - visible at sites 2.5.  Zooplankton confirmed by DNR.
Lake cleared of light chocolate color.  Cool spring.  Weed growth slow.  Water temp 62 deg F.
Large mouth bass cruising shallows for spawning sites.
Very humid + hot.  Water temp 82 deg F.
Rain 1.6" lake has been consistently high since spring.
Certain weeds that die off early are doing so.  Loons grouping up.
1.8" of rain.  Lake visibly improved since secchi reading of 9.75 on 9/5/99. Recorded 0.4" of rain.
Major beaver problem is obstructing outflow of lake.  Immature loon is present.
Beaver dam closed channel between lake this spring- water level NW bridge 82 7/16.  Barn swallows here.
Surface temp 60 degrees F.- 8 adult geese with 7 goslings. 1 pair loons nesting- 2 american mergansers.
Surface temp 60 degrees.  Survey mark 82 15/16- plate 3 1/4.
Surface temp 66 degrees F.  Survey mark 83 1/16- plate 3 1/4- dock 12 3/8 on 6/8.  Beaver dam out 6/9.
Post beaver dam removal levels: survey mark 84 3/16- plate 4 1/2- dock 13 5/8.
Dock 14 1/4"- survey mark 85"- plate 5"- lake down approximately 2 1/8".
NW survey mark 85 7/16 on 7/26/00.  Shoreline plate #1 6"- dock 15 1/2.
Dcok 14 1/2.  Loons grouping up- geese gone.
Lake is clearer this year than previous- recorded 2.0" rain previous week.  Cabbage weed is gone.
Only this years loons chick remains- adults gone.
Algae bloom appears in water- winds and cold for the last four days.  Lake appears to be going through turnover- I double checked the readings. Canada geese are back on lake.
Lake seems all churned up with dead weeds. Evidence of turnover. 5 loons observed in lake. Ice out 4-19.
1 pair of Canadian geese on lake. Suspect rest nesting in backwaters.
Water 57 deg F. 1.25" rain. Clearest water ever recorded.
Bridge survey mark 82.0". Water 62 deg F.
Survey mark at bridge 80.25". Rain 1.5" Goose count at 8 adults- 16 goslings. Beaver dams on outlet to be removed 6/20
Bridge survey mark 81.25. Water 77.4 deg F. .5" rain. 2nd loon on nest.
White cabbage weed growth behind other years. Water temp 73.4 deg F.
No rain. Back bay loon still nesting. Bridge survey mark 85"- steel plate 5 3/8"
Survey mark 85 1/8" Steel plate 5 3/8". 3/4" rain. Distinct thermocline.
Survey mark 85.5"- steel plate 5 7/8". No rain. Surface temp 84 deg F.
Satellite fly over. Cloudy. Surface temp 74 deg F.
Canadian geese = 21 flying. No longer in area.Bridge survey mark84 3/8" steel plate 5.25". Recieved 1.75" rain.
Lake cleared up- perhaps due to lack of rain.
Observed 400-500 nighthawks migrating over lake. Survey mark 85.75"- steel plate 6"
Survey mark at bridge 85 3/8"- steel plate 5 7/8". Large size algae bloom very visible. Canadian geese returning- migration gathering. Last 3 nights low 40's.
No aquatic life observable in shallows. 4-22 survey mark 80 9/16. Ice out 4-16.
Survey mark at bridge. 82 1/8. Rain 1 5/8". Water temp 48
No bluegill beds yet. Weed growth- behind other years. Pair of loons hatched 2 chicks 6/10. Some filamentous algae present.
received 5/8" rain last week. Water temp 69.
Pair of loon chicks still doing well
Steel plates have water over them.
3 adult pair of Canadian Geese and 15 goslings observed. 2 loon chicks thriving. Received 5.5" rain 1 week ago.
Some barn swallows still feeding young in nest
Barn swallows under bridge present. Had 2 nestings- 10-12 nests. 2 loon chicks almost adult size- still being fed.
Water appeared dirty and stirred up. Water 63.5. Full turnover occurring now.
Beavers are trying to dam up under Hwy 77 bridge. Snow runoff evident. Little shallow water fish life present.
Clarity of lake about normal.  Water temp 70 F.
Water temp 69 F. Here and there 2-3 mats of filamentous algae.
Water temp 75 F. Weed growth coming on fast.
Significant reduction in canada geese from 42 to 15. 6 adults- 9 gooslings. Still some clumps of filamentous algae present.
Water temp 77.9 F.  Nesting loon way overdue - fear she's dead.
Rain in part 14 days .50 inches. Observed 3 loons grouping up.  9 gooslings and 6 adult canada geese present.
Water 79 F. Mallard hatch 7 young- 2 adults. Lake down 3" from normal.
Lake levels down 3". 3-5 loons grouping on lake.
Water visibility has declined. Turnover occuring. Water 62.2 F.
No filamentous blue green algae present- cold spring- ice out approx. April 14- Lake going through turn over.
heavy pressure on pan fish spawn beds
weed growth behond this year- -cold spring
One pair of loon chicks hatched- obs - common golden-eye geese with goslings.
water 70F- more and more jet skis are now on lake
annoying jet ski noise increasing- water 74F
water 72F- received `1 inch of rain- loon groups on the lake- chicks less parenting
a few barn swallows on nest. Received 3 and one half inches of rain.
Observed 5 loons in courtship.  Cold spring.  Surface temp. 56 F.  Water levels low.  Lack of runoff and rain - county now actively managing lake levels - too low!
This lakes loons nesting.  Water 53 F.
Water 61 F- cold and cloudy weather.
No beaver sighted.  American merganser with 12 babies.  Mallards with 7 young.
Loon chick hatched and perished.  Recorded 4" rain in last 10 days.  No loon chicks this year.  Eagles
Observed 5 adult single loons swimming together.
Increasing numbers of jet skis on lake!  Recorded no rain last 10 days.  3 loons swimming in tight group.  Scattered algae clouds on bottom.
Lake always starts to undergo change now - weeds dying off.
3" of rain.  Loon chicks separated from parents.  Both loon chicks present.  New event - at least 12 common gulls taking up residence
Loon gone.  Geese coming and going.
Recorded 3 1/2" rain.  Lake very cloudy with high algae growth - actual layer on surface.
No loons.  Due to recorded 4 3/4" rain in last 10 days - large algae growth present.
Loon nesting in back bay - warmer spring than last year.
Water 75 F- no rain past 10 days.  2 loon chicks present.
Water 79 F- brood of 12 American common mergansers on lake.
No rain- algae scum beginning to appear.
Algae bloom still present - loons gone except 1 chick.
Otter observed 9/22/06.  Loons gone.  Mergansers gone - coontail at surface in some locations.
Water 62 degrees.  Enourmous section of lake bottom covering bottom.
Water 62 degrees.  Bottom algae dramatically reducing weeds.
Water 66 degrees.  Algae continues to be  major problem.
Water 73 degrees.  Lots of algae weeds.
Water 69 degrees.  Lake turning cloudy green from algae.
